SIMPLE: substance
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Substance
<hw>Sub"stance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>substantia</ets>, fr. <ets>substare</ets> to be under or present,
to stand firm; <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>stare</ets> to stand. See
<er>Stand</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which underlies all outward
manifestations; substratum; the permanent subject or cause of phenomena,
whether material or spiritual; that in which properties inhere; that
which is real, in distinction from that which is apparent; the abiding
part of any existence, in distinction from any accident; that which
constitutes anything what it is; real or existing essence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These cooks, how they stamp, and strain, and grind,⟦br⟧
And turn <qex>substance</qex> into accident!</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heroic virtue did his actions guide,⟦br⟧
And he the <qex>substance</qex>, not the appearance, chose.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The most important element in any existence; the
characteristic and essential components of anything; the main part;
essential import; purport.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This edition is the same in <qex>substance</qex> with the
Latin.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is insolent in words, in manner; but in <qex>substance</qex> it
is not only insulting, but alarming.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Body; matter; material of which a thing is made;
hence, substantiality; solidity; firmness; <as>as, the
<ex>substance</ex> of which a garment is made; some textile fabrics have
little <ex>substance</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Material possessions; estate; property;
resources.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And there wasted his <qex>substance</qex> with riotous living.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke xv. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy <qex>substance</qex>, valued at the highest rate,⟦br⟧
Can not amount unto a hundred marks.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We are destroying many thousand lives, and exhausting our
<qex>substance</qex>, but not for our own interest.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Hypostasis</er>,
2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Substance</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Substance
<hw>Sub"stance</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To furnish or endow with
substance; to supply property to; to make rich.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Substanceless</ent>⟦br⟧
